revision.text:
[[File:Aluminium_pigment_powder.JPG|thumb|right|Aluminum pigment powder]] '''Aluminum powder''' is powdered [[aluminum]]. This was originally produced by mechanical means using a [[stamp mill]] to create flakes. Subsequently, a process of spraying molten aluminum to create a powder of droplets was developed by [[E. J. Hall]] in the 1920s. The resulting powder might then be processed further in a [[ball mill]] to flatten it into flakes for use as a coating or pigment. Aluminum powder is non-toxic and is not harmful unless injected directly in a major blood vessel such as the [[Aorta|aorta]]{{citation needed|date=December 2016}}. Aluminum powder, if breathed in, is not particularly harmful and will only cause minor irritation.<ref>{{citation |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Lskj5k3PSIcC&pg=PA275 |chapter=Powder Metallurgy Processing |page=275 |title=Aluminum and Aluminum Alloys |author=Joseph R. Davies |publisher=ASM International |year=1993 |isbn=9780871704962}}</ref> The melting point of aluminum powder is 660&nbsp;°C.<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=JyNcYiY11T8C&pg=PA155&dq=The+melting+point+of+aluminum+powder+is+660%C2%A0%C2%B0C.&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiz3Zny0fDXAhVN5GMKHawuBjsQ6AEIMjAC#v=onepage&q=The%20melting%20point%20of%20aluminum%20powder%20is%20660%C2%A0%C2%B0C.&f=false|title=Principles of Fire Protection Chemistry and Physics|last=Friedman|first=Raymond|date=1998|publisher=Jones & Bartlett Learning|isbn=9780877654407|language=en}}</ref>
== Usage == * cosmetic colorant<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ewg.org/skindeep/ingredient/700324/ALUMINUM_POWDER/|title=ALUMINUM POWDER {{!}}{{!}} Skin Deep® Cosmetics Database {{!}} EWG|website=www.ewg.org|language=en|access-date=2017-12-04}}</ref> * pyrotechnic * in paints as metallic silver pigment * [[Fingerprint_powder|Fingerprint powder]]<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=n9out--0RRkC&pg=PA137&dq=Fingerprint+powder+uses+aluminum+powder&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjU4frB0fDXAhUV8GMKHWrICMYQ6AEIKDAA#v=onepage&q=Fingerprint%20powder%20uses%20aluminum%20powder&f=false|title=Fingerprints and Other Ridge Skin Impressions|last=Champod|first=Christophe|last2=Lennard|first2=Chris J.|last3=Margot|first3=Pierre|last4=Stoilovic|first4=Milutin|date=2004-04-27|publisher=CRC Press|isbn=9780203485040|language=en}}</ref> * Rocket and missile fuel * [[thermite]] * refractory Depending on the usage, the powder is either coated or uncoated.
