'''Froth treatment''' is an [[oil refining]] technique which converts [[bitumen]] recovered from [[oil sands]] into [[Dilbit|diluted bitumin]], a marketable product, which can be shipped through an [[Pipeline transport#For oil or natural gas|oil pipeline]] to an [[oil refinery]] or [[oil depot|oil terminal]]. The process removes heavier hydrocarbon compounds producing [[dilbit]] which can flow through a pipeline. The product can then be sold or upgraded further.<ref name="Alberta Oil11811">{{cite news|title=SNC-Lavalin to build $650 million froth treatment plant: Client not disclosed, but reported to be CNRL|url=http://www.albertaoilmagazine.com/2011/11/snc-lavalin-to-build-650-froth-treatment-plant/|accessdate=April 28, 2013|newspaper=Alberta Oil|date=November 8, 2011|author=Jeff Lewis}}</ref>
