The '''Sinan solar power plant''' is a 24&nbsp;MW  [[photovoltaic power station]] in [[Sinan, Jeollanam-do]], [[South Korea]]. {{As of|2009}}, it is the largest photovoltaic installation in Asia.  The project was developed by the German company [[Conergy]] and it cost US$150&nbsp;million.  It was built by the Dongyang Engineering & Construction Corporation.<ref>[http://www.exenewable.com/projectProfile.asp?id=12612 eXenewable Project Profile Page - SinAn, PV, Korea]</ref>

